  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Architectural Coordinator",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities: </p><ul><li>Carry out architectural works scheduling, material requisition, cost control, project supervision and documentation</li><li>Coordinate with Consultants, Project Manager, C&S Engineer, M&E Engineer and subcontractors to resolve construction issues to ensure timelt and smooth progress of works</li><li>Ensure quality of works and detailing are achieved and complied with safety regulation</li><li>Review drawings, specifications and method statements for compliance with codes and project requirements</li><li>Conduct site inspections to ensure compliance with local regulations and standards</li><li>Assist in project handover, defect rectifications, and TOP preparation</li><li>Attend site and coordination meetings with stakeholders</li><li>Prepare and submit reports for regulatory approvals</li><li>Any duties that may be assigned by superior or management</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Diploma / Degree in Architecture, preferably recognized by the BOA</li><li>Minimum 3 years experience in architectural finishing work in local construction industry involved in HDB/LTA/MOE projects</li><li>Experience in RI and TOP inspection procedure and documentation</li><li>Strong knowledge of Singapore building codes and regulations and familiar with local standard quality implementation</li><li>Candidates certified and registered in CONQUAS, and knowledge in Greenmark documentation will have an added advantage</li><li>Good leadership and communication skills, excellent organisational and problem-solving skills</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Remuneration shall commensurate with working experience and qualifications.</p><p>Suitable candidates are encouraged to apply to this position via Apply Now button or email to <strong>Career@kah.com.sg</strong></p><p><br /></p><p><em>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified. </em></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>",
